# Portfolio Project Standards

## Stack and style
- Use TypeScript for all app logic and React functional components.
- Keep components and pages simple, readable, and focused on one responsibility.
- Prefer existing project patterns before introducing new abstractions.

## UI and layout
- Maintain the existing clean, minimal portfolio style unless explicitly asked to redesign.
- Prefer Ant Design components where possible instead of pure HTML tags.
- Keep semantic HTML structure and accessible labels, headings, and link text.
- Ensure responsive behavior for mobile and desktop when changing layout.

## Code quality
- Favor small helper functions over repeated JSX or duplicated logic.
- Do not add dependencies unless they are clearly needed for the request.

## Safety checks before finishing
- Run or suggest relevant checks for changed code (build, lint, or type-check).
- Keep edits scoped to the request; do not refactor unrelated parts.
- Preserve existing user content and routes unless the request says otherwise.
